<question id="remove-node">
<para>
How do I remove a compute node from the cluster?
</para>
</question>

<answer>
<para>
On your frontend end, execute:
</para>

<screen>
# rocks remove host "[your compute node name]"
</screen>

<para>
For example, if the compute node's name is
<emphasis>compute-0-1</emphasis>, you'd execute:
</para>

<screen>
# rocks remove host compute-0-1
# rocks sync config
</screen>

<para>
The compute node has been removed from the cluster.
</para>

</answer>
</qandaentry>

